    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-08T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-08T21:00:00-05:00" n="720"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5004: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-09T10:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 9, 1932—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 9—2:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>424. Following from Consul General at Harbin: <pb facs="0784" n="680"
                        xml:id="pg_680"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“April 8, 5 p.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Local Japanese military mission confirms persistent Chinese
                                reports that General <persName corresp="#p_MC1">Ma
                                    Chan-shan</persName>, who left Tsitsihar on March 3rd, is now at
                                Taheiho. This would indicate that <persName corresp="#p_MC1"
                                    >Ma</persName> had given up his post as Governor at Tsitsihar
                                and Minister of War of the new régimé.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>It is believed that Japanese pursuit of <persName
                                    corresp="#p_TLGJ1">Tamon</persName>’s forces is being hampered
                                by bad condition of roads.”</item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
